tcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4629x2604+0+276/resize/600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fa9%2F6e%2F03b9aee3451eb9e8f3ab86e5665f%2Fgettyimages-1241859895.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4629x2604+0+276/resize/800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fa9%2F6e%2F03b9aee3451eb9e8f3ab86e5665f%2Fgettyimages-1241859895.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4629x2604+0+276/resize/900/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fa9%2F6e%2F03b9aee3451eb9e8f3ab86e5665f%2Fgettyimages-1241859895.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4629x2604+0+276/resize/1200/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fa9%2F6e%2F03b9aee3451eb9e8f3ab86e5665f%2Fgettyimages-1241859895.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4629x2604+0+276/resize/1600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fa9%2F6e%2F03b9aee3451eb9e8f3ab86e5665f%2Fgettyimages-1241859895.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4629x2604+0+276/resize/1800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fa9%2F6e%2F03b9aee3451eb9e8f3ab86e5665f%2Fgettyimages-1241859895.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4629x2604+0+276/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fa9%2F6e%2F03b9aee3451eb9e8f3ab86e5665f%2Fgettyimages-1241859895.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4629x2604+0+276/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fa9%2F6e%2F03b9aee3451eb9e8f3ab86e5665f%2Fgettyimages-1241859895.jpg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4629x2604+0+276/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fa9%2F6e%2F03b9aee3451eb9e8f3ab86e5665f%2Fgettyimages-1241859895.jpg" class="img" alt="The dollar has slumped more than 10% against other major currencies, marking its worst first-half a year since 1973." loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 The dollar has slumped more than 10% against other major currencies, marking its worst first-half a year since 1973.                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          Daniel Munoz/AFP via Getty Images                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The U.S. dollar serves as a significant symbol of America's financial standing. This year, the dollar has fallen more than 10%, marking its worst decline in the first six months of a year since 1973. Many investors are concerned that this decline may signal a new reality for the country. Economic confidence has been shaken by various factors, including tariffs and the country's rising debt, which is expected to increase further due to the GOP megabill that Congress passed. Here's what the &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/07/07/nx-s1-5455867/trump-dollar-value-debt-currency" target="_blank"&gt;fluctuating value of the American dollar means&lt;/a&gt;: &lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;ul class="edTag"&gt;&lt;li&gt;💵 Foreign investors have distanced themselves from the currency by selling American stocks and bonds, causing the dollar to decline. When they dump shares in a company, they sell the dollar and convert it back to their home currency.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;💵 A weaker dollar makes traveling abroad more expensive for Americans. But it is good for domestic tourism. It is also good for exporters like Apple, which earns a large portion of its revenue in other countries.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;💵 The decline in the dollar's value would make foreign products a little more expensive, which would give domestic manufacturers a leg up.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;💵 In the coming decade or two, the world may see a tri-polar system as the euro, the Chinese yuan and cryptocurrencies emerge to challenge the dollar's dominance.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;   &lt;h3 class="edTag"&gt;Picture show&lt;/h3&gt;   &lt;div id="resg-s1-75506" class="bucketwrap image large"&gt;             &lt;div     class="imagewrap has-source-dimensions"     data-crop-type=""     style="         --source-width: 5501;         --source-height: 3093;     " &gt;         &lt;picture&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5501x3093+504+991/resize/400/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F30%2F5a%2Fe0e40b754421ac7c6594c186ca47%2Fimg-2126.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5501x3093+504+991/resize/600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F30%2F5a%2Fe0e40b754421ac7c6594c186ca47%2Fimg-2126.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5501x3093+504+991/resize/800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F30%2F5a%2Fe0e40b754421ac7c6594c186ca47%2Fimg-2126.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5501x3093+504+991/resize/900/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F30%2F5a%2Fe0e40b754421ac7c6594c186ca47%2Fimg-2126.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5501x3093+504+991/resize/1200/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F30%2F5a%2Fe0e40b754421ac7c6594c186ca47%2Fimg-2126.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5501x3093+504+991/resize/1600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F30%2F5a%2Fe0e40b754421ac7c6594c186ca47%2Fimg-2126.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5501x3093+504+991/resize/1800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F30%2F5a%2Fe0e40b754421ac7c6594c186ca47%2Fimg-2126.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5501x3093+504+991/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F30%2F5a%2Fe0e40b754421ac7c6594c186ca47%2Fimg-2126.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/webp" /&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5501x3093+504+991/resize/400/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F30%2F5a%2Fe0e40b754421ac7c6594c186ca47%2Fimg-2126.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5501x3093+504+991/resize/600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F30%2F5a%2Fe0e40b754421ac7c6594c186ca47%2Fimg-2126.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5501x3093+504+991/resize/800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F30%2F5a%2Fe0e40b754421ac7c6594c186ca47%2Fimg-2126.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5501x3093+504+991/resize/900/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F30%2F5a%2Fe0e40b754421ac7c6594c186ca47%2Fimg-2126.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/st