took in close to 400 sea lions and dolphins within a few months. Unfortunately, not all of them survived. Now, the center is working to learn from their deaths and determine how the toxins affected the animals. Recently, NPR's &lt;em&gt;All Things Considered&lt;/em&gt; visited an empty beach in Palos Verdes to witness the release of one of the center's last sea lion patients. Take a look at photos showcasing the researchers' efforts, as well as the &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/sections/the-picture-show/2025/07/08/nx-s1-5453487/sea-lions-released-after-toxic-algae-california" target="_blank"&gt;release of the sea lion back into the wild&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;       &lt;h3 class="edTag"&gt;3 things to know before you go&lt;/h3&gt;   &lt;div id="resg-s1-76789" class="bucketwrap image large"&gt;             &lt;div     class="imagewrap has-source-dimensions"     data-crop-type=""     style="         --source-width: 6628;         --source-height: 3728;     " &gt;         &lt;picture&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6628x3728+0+0/resize/400/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F97%2F2c%2Ff6e139df4bc19324541fc4a3d226%2Fap25149691447696.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6628x3728+0+0/resize/600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F97%2F2c%2Ff6e139df4bc19324541fc4a3d226%2Fap25149691447696.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6628x3728+0+0/resize/800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F97%2F2c%2Ff6e139df4bc19324541fc4a3d226%2Fap25149691447696.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6628x3728+0+0/resize/900/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F97%2F2c%2Ff6e139df4bc19324541fc4a3d226%2Fap25149691447696.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false