0+0/resize/1200/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F97%2F2c%2Ff6e139df4bc19324541fc4a3d226%2Fap25149691447696.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6628x3728+0+0/resize/1600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F97%2F2c%2Ff6e139df4bc19324541fc4a3d226%2Fap25149691447696.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6628x3728+0+0/resize/1800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F97%2F2c%2Ff6e139df4bc19324541fc4a3d226%2Fap25149691447696.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6628x3728+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F97%2F2c%2Ff6e139df4bc19324541fc4a3d226%2Fap25149691447696.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6628x3728+0+0/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F97%2F2c%2Ff6e139df4bc19324541fc4a3d226%2Fap25149691447696.jpg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6628x3728+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F97%2F2c%2Ff6e139df4bc19324541fc4a3d226%2Fap25149691447696.jpg" class="img" alt="A priest during a Mass in Princeton, N.J. Catholic leaders say Mass attendance has dropped as as result of the Trump administration&amp;#039;s immigration actions. (AP Photo/Luis Andres Henao)" loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 A priest during a Mass in Princeton, N.J. Catholic leaders say Mass attendance has dropped as as result of the Trump administration's immigration actions. (AP Photo/Luis Andres Henao)                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          Luis Andres Henao/AP                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;ol class="edTag"&gt;&lt;li&gt;The Diocese of San Bernardino is the first diocese in the U.S. to formally lift the obligation for Catholics to attend Mass due to &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/07/09/nx-s1-5462837/diocese-of-san-bernardino-issues-dispensation-saying-catholics-who-fear-ice-dont-have-to-attend-mass" target="_blank"&gt;concerns over immigration detentions&lt;/a&gt; happening on church property.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Sean Combs' &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/07/09/g-s1-76709/sean-combs-sentencing-date-set" target="_blank"&gt;sentencing date has been set&lt;/a&gt; to Oct. 3 after the music mogul was found guilty of two counts of transportation for prostitution last week, according to a letter endorsed by U.S. District Judge Arun Subramanian.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Linda Yaccarino, CEO of X, announced yesterday she is &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/07/09/nx-s1-5462728/x-linda-yaccarino-elon-musk" target="_blank"&gt;stepping down from the social media platform&lt;/a&gt; after two years in the role.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;This newsletter was edited by &lt;/em&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/people/859721331/suzanne-nuyen"target="_blank"   &gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Suzanne Nuyen&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;</description>
