/&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2121x1193+0+221/resize/400/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fd7%2F84%2Fd114af31417388b333441bbb77a7%2Fgettyimages-492675508.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2121x1193+0+221/resize/600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fd7%2F84%2Fd114af31417388b333441bbb77a7%2Fgettyimages-492675508.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2121x1193+0+221/resize/800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fd7%2F84%2Fd114af31417388b333441bbb77a7%2Fgettyimages-492675508.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2121x1193+0+221/resize/900/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fd7%2F84%2Fd114af31417388b333441bbb77a7%2Fgettyimages-492675508.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2121x1193+0+221/resize/1200/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fd7%2F84%2Fd114af31417388b333441bbb77a7%2Fgettyimages-492675508.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2121x1193+0+221/resize/1600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fd7%2F84%2Fd114af31417388b333441bbb77a7%2Fgettyimages-492675508.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2121x1193+0+221/resize/1800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fd7%2F84%2Fd114af31417388b333441bbb77a7%2Fgettyimages-492675508.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2121x1193+0+221/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fd7%2F84%2Fd114af31417388b333441bbb77a7%2Fgettyimages-492675508.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2121x1193+0+221/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fd7%2F84%2Fd114af31417388b333441bbb77a7%2Fgettyimages-492675508.jpg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2121x1193+0+221/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fd7%2F84%2Fd114af31417388b333441bbb77a7%2Fgettyimages-492675508.jpg" class="img" alt="Seed oils, commonly called vegetable oils, are extracted from the seeds of plants." loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 Seed oils, commonly called vegetable oils, are extracted from the seeds of plants.                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          alaskla/iStockphoto/Getty Images                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Living Better is a &lt;/em&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/series/1176326550/living-better" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;em&gt;special series&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;em&gt; about what it takes to stay healthy in America.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Seed oils are bad for you, according to Kennedy. The health secretary said vegetable oils, like canola and soybean, are poisoning Americans and driving the obesity epidemic. Kennedy points to obesity rates climbing as seed oils began to dominate the American diet as part of the evidence for his claim. Many researchers say seed oils may not be as good for you as olive oil, but the claims that they are harmful to health have been stretched too far. Check out what the &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/07/07/nx-s1-5453769/nutrition-canola-rfk-seed-oils-soybean" target="_blank"&gt;science has to say&lt;/a&gt;: &lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;ul class="edTag"&gt;&lt;li&gt;➡️ To maximize oil extraction from seeds, manufacturers often use heat and chemicals. Critics are concerned about hexane, a hazardous solvent used in refining. However, the residues are at levels too low to be toxic.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;➡️ A common argument against seed oils is that they promote inflammation because they contain higher levels of essential fatty acids known as omega-6s. However, randomized controlled trials have demonstrated that when people consume more seed oils, they don't show increased levels of pro-inflammatory compounds in their tissues.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;➡️ Seed oils are prevalent in ultra-processed foods, which make up a significant portion of the U.S. food supply. Rather than focusing on which oils to consume, the focal point should be a person's overall diet, says Christopher Gardner, a nutrition scientist and professor of medicine at Stanford University.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;       &lt;h3 class="edTag"&gt;Picture show&lt;/h3&gt;   &lt;div id="resg-s1-64963" class="bucketwrap image large"&gt;             &lt;div     class="imagewrap has-source-dimensions"     data-crop-type=""     style="         --source-width: 2174;         --source-height: 1223;     " &gt;         &lt;picture&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2174x1223+531+819/resize/400/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F49%2F3c%2Fbd68383242b78825717f909dffcb%2Fpapilio-9780593693254-4.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2174x1223+531+819/resize/600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F49%2F3c%2Fbd68383242b78825717f909dffcb%2Fpapilio-9780593693254-4.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2174x1223+531+819/resize/800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F49%2F3c%2Fbd68383242b78825717f909dffcb%2Fpapilio-9780593693254-4.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2174x1223+531+819/resize/900/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F49%2F3c%2Fbd68383242b78825717f909dffcb%2Fpapilio-9780593693254-4.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2174x1223+531+819/resize/1200/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F49%2F3c%2Fbd68383242b78825717f909dffcb%2Fpapilio-9780593693254-4.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2174x1223+531+819/resize/1600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F49%2F3c%2Fbd68383242b78825717f909dffcb%2Fpapilio-9780593693254-4.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2174x1223+531+819/resize/1800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F49%2F3c%2Fbd68383242b78825717f909dffcb%2Fpapilio-9780593693254-4.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2174x1223+531+819/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F49%2F3c%2Fbd68383242b78825717f909dffcb%2Fpapilio-9780593693254-4.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/webp" /&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2174x1223+531+819/resize/400/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F49%2F3c%2Fbd68383242b78825717f909dffcb%2Fpapilio-9780593693254-4.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2174x1223+531+819/resize/600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F49%2F3c%2Fbd68383242b78825717f909dffcb%2Fpapilio-9780593693254-4.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2174x1223+531+819/resize/800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F49%2F3c%2Fbd68383242b78825717f909dffcb%2Fpapilio-9780593693254-4.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2174x1223+531+819/resize/900/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F49%2F3c%2Fbd68383242b78825717f909dffcb%2Fpapilio-9780593693254-4.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2174x1223+531+819/resize/1200/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F49%2F3c%2Fbd68383242b78825717f909dffcb%2Fpapilio-9780593693254-4.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2174x1223+531+819/resize/1600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F49%2F3c%2Fbd68383242b78825717f909dffcb%2Fpapilio-9780593693254-4.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2174x1223+531+819/resize/1800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F49%2F3c%2Fbd68383242b78825717f909dffcb%2Fpapilio-9780593693254-4.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2174x1223+531+819/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F49%2F3c%2Fbd68383242b78825717f909dffcb%2Fpapilio-9780593693254-4.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2174x1223+531+819/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F49%2F3c%2Fbd68383242b78825717f909dffcb%2Fpapilio-9780593693254-4.jpg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2174x1223+531+819/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F49%2F3c%2Fbd68383242b78825717f909dffcb%2Fpapilio-9780593693254-4.jpg" class="img" alt="Papilio_9780593693254_4.jpg" loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Papilio&lt;/em&gt; is a picture book told in three parts, each highlighting a different stage of a butterfly's life (there are technically four stages for a butterfly's life, but the egg stage isn't particularly exciting). The three friends who wrote and illustrated the story felt that those three stages were the perfect way to justify the collaboration. Throughout the book, the authors, Ben Clanton, Corey R. Tabor and Andy Chou Musser, were able to display their own voices and illustration styles by each taking on one phase. At its core, the story explores themes of change, transformation and growing up. One key lesson readers can take away is that it's OK to ask for help as you grow up. Explore each butterfly life stage further from the authors' perspectives and view &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/07/05/nx-s1-5253034/papilio-ben-clanton-corey-tabor-andy-chou-musser" target="_blank"&gt;photos from the book here&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;h3 class="edTag"&gt;3 things to know before you go&lt;/h3&gt;   &lt;div id="resg-s1-76454" class="bucketwrap image large"&gt;             &lt;div     class="imagewrap has-source-dimensions"     data-crop-type=""     style="         --source-width: 1760;         --source-height: 990;     " &gt;         &lt;picture&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1760x990+0+92/resize/400/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F57%2F33%2Fbed317654203b86dd46b499d12a2%2Fimage-2025-07-07t164937-037.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1760x990+0+92/resize/600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F57%2F33%2Fbed317654203b86dd46b499d12a2%2Fimage-2025-07-07t164937-037.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1760x990+0+92/resize/800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F57%2F33%2Fbed317654203b86dd46b499d12a2%2Fimage-2025-07-07t164937-037.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1760x990+0+92/resize/900/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F57%2F33%2Fbed317654203b86dd46b499d12a2%2Fimage-2025-07-07t164937-037.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1760x990+0+92/resize/1200/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F57%2F33%2Fbed317654203b86dd46b499d12a2%2Fimage-2025-07-07t164937-037.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1760x990+0+92/resize/1600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F57%2F33%2Fbed317654203b86dd46b499d12a2%2Fimage-2025-07-07t164937-037.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1760x990+0+92/resize/1800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F57%2F33%2Fbed317654203b86dd46b499d12a2%2Fimage-2025-07-07t164937-037.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1760x990+0+92/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F57%2F33%2Fbed317654203b86dd46b499d12a2%2Fimage-2025-07-07t164937-037.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/webp" /&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1760x990+0+92/resize/400/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F57%2F33%2Fbed317654203b86dd46b499d12a2%2Fimage-2025-07-07t164937-037.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1760x990+0+92/resize/600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F57%2F33%2Fbed317654203b86dd46b499d12a2%2Fimage-2025-07-07t164937-037.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1760x990+0+92/resize/800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F57%2F33%2Fbed317654203b86dd46b499d12a2%2Fimage-2025-07-07t164937-037.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1760x990+0+92/resize/900/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F57%2F33%2Fbed317654203b86dd46b499d12a2%2Fimage-2025-07-07t164937-037.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1760x990+0+92/resize/1200/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F57%2F33%2Fbed317654203b86dd46b499d12a2%2Fimage-2025-07-07t164937-037.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1760x990+0+92/resize/1600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F57%2F33%2Fbed317654203b86dd46b499d12a2%2Fimage-2025-07-07t164937-037.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1760x990+0+92/resize/1800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F57%2F33%2Fbed317654203b86dd46b499d12a2%2Fimage-2025-07-07t164937-037.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1760x990+0+92/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F57%2F33%2Fbed317654203b86dd46b499d12a2%2Fimage-2025-07-07t164937-037.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1760x990+0+92/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F57%2F33%2Fbed317654203b86dd46b499d12a2%2Fimage-2025-07-07t164937-037.jpg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1760x990+0+92/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F57%2F33%2Fbed317654203b86dd46b499d12a2%2Fimage-2025-07-07t164937-037.jpg" class="img" alt="Three American flamingos wade in the shallow waters of Garfield Bight in the Everglades as they forage for food." loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 Three American flamingos wade in the shallow waters of Garfield Bight in the Everglades as they forage for food.                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          &lt;i&gt;Courtesy of Dr. Mark Ian Cook&lt;/i&gt;/WLRN                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;ol class="edTag"&gt;&lt;li&gt;A flock of 125 American flamingos was observed in the Everglades last week. This &lt;a href="https://www.wlrn.org/environment/2025-07-07/flamingos-florida-bay-everglades" target="_blank"&gt;marks one of the largest groups&lt;/a&gt; of American flamingos in a decade. (via &lt;a href="https://www.wlrn.org/" target="_blank"&gt;WLRN&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Claire Schwartz is on a &lt;a href="https://www.kqed.org/news/12043312/in-la-a-photo-detective-reunites-wildfire-survivors-with-lost-images" target="_blank"&gt;mission to reunite spared, treasured items&lt;/a&gt; such as old family photos, children's artwork, old sheet music, and yearbook pages from the deadly Palisades and Eaton fires in January with their owners. (via &lt;a href="https://www.kqed.org/" target="_blank"&gt;KQED&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;After a falling tree branch left him paralyzed, Google engineer Sasha Blair-Goldensohn began &lt;a href="https://www.wbur.org/hereandnow/2025/06/30/google-engineer-accessibility" target="_blank"&gt;helping people with disabilities navigate&lt;/a&gt; cities by highlighting wheelchair-accessible public transit routes and "walking" paths on the company's maps. (via &lt;a href="https://www.wbur.org/" target="_blank"&gt;WBUR&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;This newsletter was edited by&lt;/em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt; &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/people/859721331/suzanne-nuyen"target="_blank"   &gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Suzanne Nuyen&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;em&gt;.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;</description>
